<span id="freeTextContainer11113295091919260505">I could not put this book down from the moment I began to read. The characters are beautifully drawn out, and the writing superb. It&apos;s one of those books where the story just stays with you. Life in Bombay with it&apos;s sharp lines between poverty and wealth. The significance of the educated over the uneducated. The trials and hardships of women dominated by men. The main character of this book has been a servant to a higher class and well educated family for so many years the ties become as strong </span>
  <span id="freeText11113295091919260505" style="display:none">I could not put this book down from the moment I began to read. The characters are beautifully drawn out, and the writing superb. It's one of those books where the story just stays with you. Life in Bombay with it's sharp lines between poverty and wealth. The significance of the educated over the uneducated. The trials and hardships of women dominated by men. The main character of this book has been a servant to a higher class and well educated family for so many years the ties become as strong as family. Yet with their class discrepancies do they really know one another? When one is betrayed are blood ties more meaningful than family ties? This book tackles so many deep questions while also being a simple story of daily life. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11113295091919260505" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

